Review: i love jake johnson and anna kendrick but this never fully gelled for me. it felt like the script needed another draft - there wasn't enough character development for me to be invested in the romance and it was truly all over the place.

i cackled - and cried! - this was deeply funny and weirdly moving. the four leads are excellent, with some of the best buddy chemistry i think i've ever seen. i do think it loses a little steam in the last third or so - but the rest is so fun that i don't even care!

Movie: The Hunger Games: The Ballad of Songbirds & Snakes
Review: i still think the same things that don't work very well in the book (namely the pacing) don't work here, but i was completely captivated from start to finish and thought the performances were good. it LOOKED gorgeous.
mandy moore's performance in this is proof that you can become a better actor with practice and work, and shane west's is proof that you have to want to!
very good performances and lots to chew on here, but i think it's like 30 minutes too long (sorry)!
i don't have anything profound or unique to say but uh yeah this was pretty incredible

really moving and upsetting and handled with such care for its central character. i was riveted watching her become increasingly isolated from literally everyone at such a young age. what a heartbreaker of a movie.
what the fuck was that third act?

a bit uneven tbh but i laughed a lot and i thought the chemistry was great, even if i couldn't stop thinking about that meme that said glen powell looks like a capybara that made a wish to become human.

Movie: Home Alone 2: Lost in New York
Review: i remember really loving this as child, though i suspect a lot of that was wanting to stay in a fancy hotel. this was darker and more violent than i remembered and doesn't quite capture the magic of the first. still fun, though.
much more fun than i remembered, but his family still feels like the biggest bunch of assholes!
